{
  "id": 5152759609425920,
  "name": "trigger-scope",
  "summary": "trigger-scope gives authors the ability to limit the names of animation triggers declared by trigger-instantiating properties.\n\nTrigger-Instantiating properties, such as timeline-trigger, declare names which can be referenced by the animation-trigger property in order to attach animations to triggers. However, these names are global by default (similar to anchor-name) and it is often useful for author to limit the visibility of the names so as to isolate animation-to-trigger interactions.",
